						               													<description>Waves of aliens are attacking the planet. After the last spaceship of the invaders arrive you have limited time to destroy all your enemies or they will manage to send a message to their home planet to send more reinforcements. You must build your defense so it will hold until the last spaceship is destroyed.&amp;#10;The difficulty level of the game is set by the invaders wave layout. Changing the layout can change the whole game flow and make it more challenging.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played using hex map and the units are counter that use the classic A-D-M indication.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Flow&amp;#10;The turn is constructed from the following phases&amp;#10;Activate aliens: Activate the current turn invading aliens by turning this turn aliens and placing them on board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Reinforcement: The player receives reinforcements points that can be used to buy units and buy factories that will be placed on the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Activate: The player receives energy points that will be used to move the units that are already on board, energies units and launch defend satellites.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Move aliens: Move the aliens based on their attributes toward the cities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Combat: If there are adjacent aliens forces to the defending forces then combat occurs between them.&amp;#10;Combat is done using D6 and a hit is determined if the result is lower or equal then the power of the unit attacking.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After the tenth turn end of game is checked:&amp;#10;The player wins if he eliminates all the invading aliens&amp;#10;The player loses if there are still invading aliens after the 15th turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game participated in the BGG 2018 war game print and play contest and won the following awards:&amp;#10;2nd Place: Best Solitaire Game&amp;#10;3rd Place: Best Game in this year's theme: SCI-FI &amp;amp; FANTASY&amp;#10;3rd Place: Best Short/Quick/Small Game&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
